column4: I don't know how many here read french I don't can you you give a bit of s description in english.

There is a out of the bios boot from menu mine is triggered with f12 at powering on yours may be the same or different.
I don't PM the channel is your best help, and I would not just PM without asking in the future. ;)
Did you understand my reference to the out of the bios bot menu? Some do not realize this option, it allows you to not change the bios to boot another HD or usb or cd....etc.
: Yes, F9 is for boot menu, and i've press ESC for select device for boot
Hmm that worked?
I use the arrow keys to move to the device to boot then enter.
: yes yes, After there is a hyphen that appears top left of the screen flashes. And then the CD should start. But it does not work and the pc boot to HD
THis cd has worked on this computer?
: no it's an other CD, but same configuration and same brand
: and with an other computer I've check files, all are present
Could it be a burned to fast or md5sum problem, or just a bad burn in general?
I would use a usb myself, but cd's are cheap if you have empty ones check the md5sum of the ISO and burn it slow as an image.
: I left to choose the burning speed by software. And the image was already burned to another CD and ran.

Sometimes using a what seems a good cause and effect is not really the answer to success, I would md5sum check the ISO, tell us if you do not know what that means and try another slowest burn possible or a usb.
: md5sum is good, I go burn slowly
Cool good luck, ;)
Thanks, but wich speed is good for burn it ?
Most burners go pretty fast these days I would just choose the slowest option.
